# Artificial Neural Network

- data $\longrightarrow$ features $\longrightarrow$ deterministic/probabilistic classifications/predictions $\longrightarrow$ decision
  - everyday examples
    - weather report $\longrightarrow$ clothes tomorrow
    - price from competitors $\longrightarrow$ buy here or elsewhere
- feature space
  - ![feature space](../../../ronzz-img/public/img/brilliant-graphics/capture_24-12-2025-17-06-37.png)
  - $\sum_{i=0}^{n}w_ix_i \ge b $
- binary neuron
  - $
    y = 
    \begin{cases}
    1 & \text{if } \sum_{k=1}^{n} w_k x_k - b \ge 0 \\
    0 & \text{otherwise}
    \end{cases}
    $

- sigmoid neuron
  - ![sigmoid neuron](../../../ronzz-img/public/img/brilliant-graphics/sigmoid-neuron.gif)
  - ![sigmoid neuron](../../../ronzz-img/public/img/brilliant-graphics/sigmoid-neuron-2.gif)
  - sigmoid functions
    - general form : $O=\sigma((\sum I_iw_i)-b)$
    - most common : $O=\frac{1}{1+e^{b-(\sum I_iw_i)}}$
    - ![sigmoid functions](/home/rongzhou/Documents/ronzz-img/public/img/brilliant-graphics/capture_24-12-2025-18-38-27.png)
    - error tolerance
  - parameters
    - bias
    - input weight
- identity neuron
  - $O=(\sum I_iw_i)-b$

